HOUSE RULES

Check-in Instructions
Check-in instructions will be sent the day of arrival and your door code access will be provided 1 hour prior to check in. If you have not already secured early check-in, pool heat, or late check-out, please feel free to message us for availability and associated fees.

Home Essentials
To get you started on your vacation we provide each home with a Housekeeping Starter Kit which includes several rolls of paper towels, dishwasher pods, dishwashing soap, trash bags, laundry pods, several rolls of toilet paper per restroom, shampoo, conditioner, and body wash dispensers in all the showers. Towel sets and pool towels are included on each bed.

Kitchen & Coffee
All of our homes are equipped with full kitchens along with standard cookware and glassware. We do not provide any food essentials such as oils and spices. With this in mind, we recommend bringing your supplies and everything you need on vacation. Each home has a coffee maker/keurig. We supply filters and several coffee pods to get you started your first morning.

Noise Ordinance
Noise levels are monitored during quiet hours from 10pm to 8am. Please note there is a city ordinance monitored by code enforcement that prohibits parties in vacation rentals. If a noise complaint is made, A FEE OF $1,000.00 WILL BE ASSESSED, and TENANTS MAY BE ASKED TO VACATE PROPERTY, WITH NO REFUNDS. If the police are contacted by neighbors, it could result in A FINE OF UP TO $5,000.00 and IMMEDIATE EVICTION WITH NO REFUNDS.

See you out there,
Duggan
